wikipedia_page.main: Robert Christopher Travers (born 18 March 1982) is an English cricketer who made a single List A appearance for Somerset Cricket Board in 2001. He has played for Glastonbury Cricket Club since 2001, and has been captain of the side since 2009. He is a right-arm off break bowler, and lower-order right-handed batsman.
